# Templecurraheen Graveyard Project Structure

This is an Eleventy (11ty) static site generator project for documenting the Templecurraheen Graveyard heritage site.

## Key Files and Architecture

### Configuration Files

- [eleventy.config.js](mdc:eleventy.config.js) - Main Eleventy configuration with custom filters and collections
- [tailwind.config.js](mdc:tailwind.config.js) - Tailwind CSS configuration with custom color scheme
- [package.json](mdc:package.json) - Dependencies and build scripts

### Source Structure

- [src/](mdc:src/) - All source files for the website
- [src/\_layouts/](mdc:src/_layouts/) - Nunjucks templates (base.njk, grave.njk)
- [src/\_data/](mdc:src/_data/) - Data files including gallery.json and burials.tsv
- [src/graves/](mdc:src/graves/) - Individual grave/burial record markdown files
- [src/css/styles.css](mdc:src/css/styles.css) - Tailwind CSS source file

### Build Output

- [\_site/](mdc:_site/) - Generated static site (do not edit directly)

## Development Workflow

### Starting Development Server

Always use `npm start` (not `npm run dev`) which runs:

- Tailwind CSS compilation in watch mode
- Eleventy development server with live reload
- Both processes run concurrently for full functionality

### CSS Architecture

- Uses Tailwind CSS with custom stone color palette
- CSS must be compiled by Tailwind before serving
- Raw `@tailwind` directives in source, compiled CSS in `_site/css/`

## Data Management

### Gallery Images

Images are managed through [src/\_data/gallery.json](mdc:src/_data/gallery.json) with categories:

- `general` - Overall graveyard views, entrance, grounds
- `headstones` - Individual graves and monuments
- `historical` - Archive photos and documentation

### Burial Records

- Individual grave files in [src/graves/](mdc:src/graves/) use `grave.njk` layout
- Burial data in [src/\_data/burials.tsv](mdc:src/_data/burials.tsv)
- Each grave file requires proper frontmatter with layout, name, dates, etc.
